Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

2:02 PM Apprs: CO: S. Needham, Rpr: Kasten, Clerk: Lindabaur. Prosecuting attorney Holly Elkin Rockow in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Melissa Martinez did not appear. State requests statewide body only warrant; so ordered. Recalled at 2:12 PM. Prosecuting attorney Holly Elkin Rockow in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Melissa Martinez in court.  Attorney Abrianna Dolfi in court for Melissa Martinez. DE states she was calling the public defender's office. DE states she just moved, but will update her address ASAP. Court quashes warrant. DE qualifies for PD. Court informs Defendant of charges, possible penalties and rights. Defendant understands. Waive reading. NG. Bond argument; bond ordered. Settlement conference to be held prior to 8/10/22.
Pre-trial/scheduling conference scheduled for September 1, 2022 at 08:30 am.

It is hereby ordered, as a condition of the defendant's bond/bail in the above-captioned case, that he/she have absolutely NO CONTACT whatsoever with the complaining witness, or with any of the following named persons and/or locations, Fireworks Outlet in Baldwin, WI.  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as no contact in person, by telephone, by way of electronic device, email, facsimile, social media including but not limited to texting, Facebook, Twitter, contact through the mail, and/or through a third person.  The aforementioned condition of bond/bail is set pursuant to Sec. 969.02(3)(d), Wis Stats.

If the defendant fails to comply with the conditions of his/her bond/bail that he/she may be charged with the offense of bail jumping.
Pre-trial/scheduling conference on September 1, 2022 at 08:30 am.
